    Downloads data using download handler

    download_data.Rd

    This function downloads measurements for a specific time range and adds these to the database. Depending on the source (e.g. an API) of the data, a download handler is needed. This download handler is a function wich get's the data for the time range and returns a data.frame with using a specific format.

    download_data(station, Tstart, Tend, fun, conn)

    Arguments

    station

    station id

    Tstart

    start of time range

    Tend

    end of time range

    fun

    name of function to use as downloadhandler

    conn

    database connection object

    Value

    a data.frame with the downloaded measurements or NULL if no measurements are downloaded

    This function does three things. It first determines which (parts of the) time ranges are missing from the database. Next, it will download the missing data. Third, it adds the data to the database and updates the table wich the available time ranges

    This function uses a seperate function as download handler. Depending on the source (file, database or API) a specific function must be available
